metadata:
  section_id: 25
  section_name: رسول مقبول صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کے کھانا کھانے کا بیان
  hadith_first: 133
  hadith_last: 138

hadiths[6]{hadithnumber,text,grades,reference,international_number,narrator_chain,chapter_intro}:
133,"""I saw Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) leaning on a cushion.”",,,133,"Jabir ibn Samura said:",رسول مقبول صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کے کھانا کھانے کا بیان
134,"“The Prophet (Allah bless him and give him peace) was feeling ill, so he came out leaning on Usama ibn Zaid wearing an outer garment of coarse cotton fabric, which he had thrown on loosely, after which he led them in the ritual prayer.”",,,134,"Anas said:",رسول مقبول صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کے کھانا کھانے کا بیان
135,"""I went in to see Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) during his illness in which he died, and on his head there was a yellow band. I greeted him with the salutation of peace, so he said: 'O Fadl!”'I said: 'Doubly at your service, O Messenger of Allah!' He said: 'Wrap my head firmly with this band!' I acted accordingly, then he sat and placed the palm of his hand on my shoulder. Then he stood up and entered the mosque.” (This tradition is part of a longer story.)",,,135,"Al-Fadl ibn Abbas said:",رسول مقبول صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کے کھانا کھانے کا بیان
136,"""The Prophet (Allah bless him and give him peace) used to lick his fingers three times.”",,,136,"Reported on the authority of Ibn al-Ka'b ibn Malik, that his father said:",رسول مقبول صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کے کھانا کھانے کا بیان
137,"“When the Prophet (Allah bless him and give him peace) ate a meal, he used to lick his three fingers [the thumb, the index finger and the middle finger].”",,,137,"Anas said:",رسول مقبول صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کے کھانا کھانے کا بیان
138,"“The Prophet said (Allah bless him and give him peace): 'As for me, I do not eat while leaning on a support'!”",,,138,"Abu Juhaifa said:",رسول مقبول صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کے کھانا کھانے کا بیان
